The article discusses the recent bipartisan vote in Congress, which saw a historic number of women expressing their support for gender equality. The author reflects on their personal experience as a young Senate candidate fighting for the Equal Rights Amendment (ERA) nearly 50 years ago, emphasizing the importance of enshrining gender equality in the Constitution. They argue that gender equality is not only a moral issue but also crucial for economic prosperity, national security, and the health of democracy. The author highlights the current challenges faced by women due to the COVID-19 pandemic and calls for renewed efforts to dismantle systemic barriers and provide equal opportunities for all Americans.